org.hkijena.jipipe.api.compat

Interface ImageJDatatypeAdapter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CLIJImageDataImageJAdapter, ImgPlusDataImageJAdapter, OMEImageDataImageJAdapter, PathDataImageJAdapter, ResultsTableDataImageJAdapter, ROIDataImageJAdapter

    public interface ImageJDatatypeAdapter
    Interface that contains functions that allow conversion between JIPipe and ImageJ data type

      • convertJIPipeToImageJ

        Object convertJIPipeToImageJ(JIPipeData jipipeData,
                             boolean activate,
                             boolean noWindow,
                             String windowName)
        Converts a JIPipe data type to its corresponding ImageJ data type
        Parameters:
        jipipeData - JIPipe data
        activate - If true, the data should be made visible in ImageJ
        noWindow - If true, the conversion should not create GUI windows
        windowName - Window name of the ImageJ data. Might be ignored or used otherwise to identify data.
        Returns:
        Converted object

      • convertMultipleJIPipeToImageJ

        List<Object> convertMultipleJIPipeToImageJ(List<JIPipeData> jipipeData,
                                           boolean activate,
                                           boolean noWindow,
                                           String windowName)
        Converts multiple JIPipe data to their corresponding ImageJ data type. This method is actually called by the single algorithm run, as some data might need to be condensed
        Parameters:
        jipipeData - JIPipe data
        activate - If true, the data should be made visible in ImageJ
        noWindow - If true, the conversion should not create GUI windows
        windowName - Window name of the ImageJ data. Might be ignored or used otherwise to identify data.
        Returns:
        Converted object
